sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64750
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeffrey J Tabor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter is activated when functional SPI-1 type III secretion systems are present and functional in Salmonella typhimurium 1344.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter includes the binding site for the transcription factor InvF. This transcription factor is activated by the SicA chaparone when the secretion system is active.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was cloned from Salmonella typhimurium 1344 genomic DNA.

Construction of  basic part K112707

PCR of dv017/dv016 on pBca1037         (499bp, EcoRI/BamHI/DpnI)
Sub into pBca1256                       (EcoRI/BamHI, 2472+499, L)
Product is pBca1256-K112707
-----------------------------------------------
dv017 Forward biobricking of 
cgataGAATTCatgAGATCTaGATCCTGTGATGTTTGGCG

dv016 Reverse biobricking of 
cgttaGGATCCGATAATGTtTGCAGGGGAATTATTTTG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The sicA promoter is a regulatory element in the Salmonella SPI-1 secretion system. It controls the expression of secreted effector proteins in the natural system and turns on late. Please reference Temme et al, 2008, JMB for exact dynamics of this promoter and associated feedback mechanisms. This promoter only functions in Salmonella strains containing SPI-1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part can only be used in salmonella strains.
